1667d06503eaaaf6,Gabriel from DataCamp ,How Is Content Created At DataCamp?,2018-10-16,"Content Library Growth in the Past 3 Months, Project Jupyter and Interactive Computing, Pandas Resampling Tutorial, Data Visualization In Python Using Bokeh, and more! DataCamp ISSUE #67 — OCTOBER 16,","[

Content Library Growth in the Past 3 Months, Project Jupyter and Interactive Computing, Pandas Resampling Tutorial, Data Visualization In Python Using Bokeh, and more!

Hi there - this week's newsletter starts off with a blog post on the team behind the content at DataCamp, followed by an overview of the content we've released in Q3 this year, and what’s coming next. All of our content is designed to make it easier to learn, practice, and apply the data science skills you’ll use in your career. We also have a new podcast episode out and wanted to share a couple of finance and neural network tutorials, a pandas resampling tutorial, and much more from our Community!
New DataFramed Episode! Learn about data science, interactive computing, open source software, and Project Jupyter with Brian Granger (co-founder of Project Jupyter).
How Is Content Created At DataCamp? ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/blog/how-content-is-created-datacamp )
In this blog, learn about the team behind the screen that helps create the courses, practice exercises, and projects here at DataCamp.
Our Content Library Growth in the Past 3 Months ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/blog/content-q3 )
In this post, DataCamp co-founder Martijn Theuwissen reflects on the new content we launched in Q3 2018 and looks ahead to what’s coming in Q4.
VGG16 And Its Implementation Using Keras ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/all-about-vgg16-and-its-implementation-using-keras-noawfmi3ze )

Karen Simonyan and Andrew Zisserman investigated the effect of convolutional network depth on the accuracy of large-scale image recognition. They named their findings VGG16 (Visual Geometry Group) and VGG19. Read about VGG16 and its implementation using Keras in this article.
Data Visualization In Python Using Bokeh ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/data-visualization-in-python-using-bokeh-4qf12eb0qiw )
Data visualization is one of the key functions of a data scientist. Drawing on context from algorithmic trading, this article explains how one can visualize data in Python using Bokeh.
Implementing AlexNet CNN Architecture Using Keras ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-implement-alexnet-cnn-architecture-using-keras-7vq9ilt9qb7 )

Alex Krizhevsky, Geoffrey Hinton, and Ilya Sutskever created a neural network architecture called 'AlexNet' and won the Image Classification Challenge (ILSVRC) in 2012. In this article, you will learn how to implement AlexNet architecture using Keras.
Backtesting Long Short Moving Average Crossover Strategy in Excel ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/backtesting-long-short-moving-average-crossover-strategy-in-excel-qf8uag4tyj )
Learn how to build the 'Hello World' of trading strategies: the Long Short Moving Average Crossover Strategy.
Converting Tick-By-Tick Data To OHLC Data Using Pandas Resample ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/converting-tick-by-tick-data-to-ohlc-data-using-pandas-resample-yx9hbxo919e )
In this pandas resample tutorial, see how to use the pandas package to convert tick by tick data to Open, High, Low, and Close data in python.
Connecting FXCM Over FIX - A Detailed Tutorial ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/connecting-fxcm-over-fix-a-detailed-tutorial-vcbocuf3h2m )
This article introduces you to the Financial Information Exchange (FIX) protocol, and how you can leverage QuickFIX as a messaging engine to manage communication on top of FIX.
This blog post is an introduction to zipline in Python. It covers the zipline package, highlighting some of its benefits, how to install it, and more!
5 Rising Trends Disrupting the 2018 Analytics Hiring Market ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/5-rising-trends-disrupting-the-2018-analytics-hiring-market-ebj1bs7gjl )

Burtch Works looked at which current trends are shaking up the analytics hiring market this year, including their implications for both professionals and employers, as well as two trends on the horizon that are set to shake up the market in a big way.
That's all for now. Have a great week!
DataCamp Inc. | 350 Fifth Avenue | Suite 7730 | New York, NY 10118

column2:
re diving into","[

Contingency analysis, TensorFlow tutorial for beginners, recommended IDEs for data scientists and much more!

column1: Happy Tuesday! This week we're diving into contingency analysis in R, a TensorFlow tutorial for beginners, recommended IDEs for data scientists and much more!

We also have a new episode of DataFramed! Andrew Gelman, professor of statistics and political science, and director of the Applied Statistics Center at Columbia University, speaks with Hugo about statistics, data science, polling, and election forecasting.
In this tutorial, you'll learn with the help of an example how 'Contingency Analysis' or 'Chi-square test of independence works and also how efficiently you can run it using R.
In this TensorFlow beginner tutorial, you'll learn how to build a neural network step-by-step and how to train, evaluate and optimize it.
Step-by-step Implementation of CNN using Keras ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-implement-cnn-using-keras-step-by-step-epkonoygd1r )
In this module, you will check out the implementation of CNN using Keras on MNIST dataset and then you will compare the results with the regular neural network.
Pairs Trading on ETF EPAT Project Work ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/pairs-trading-on-etf-epat-project-work-tqr52uv1fdn )
This project covers building a portfolio using 3 ETF pairs in oil (USO vs XLE), technology (XLK vs IYW), and financial sectors (XLF vs PSCF).

Yann LeCun proposed a neural network architecture for handwritten and machine-printed character recognition in the 1990s which he called LeNet-5. The architecture is straightforward and simple to understand which is why it is mostly used as the first step for teaching Convolutional Neural Networks.

The real effective exchange rate (REER) is the weighted average of a country's currency in relation to a basket of other currencies. This article talks about Real Effective Exchange Rates and how they are useful in measuring whether a currency has appreciated relative to its trading partners.
Data Science 2018 Recap: Salaries, Hiring Trends, and Predictions ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/data-science-2018-recap-salaries-hiring-trends-and-predictions-up0b8olnajf )

This 13-minute video shares the top insights from our new 2018 data science salary report, including compensation trends, developing hiring market trends, and our predictions for where the field is headed.
Aroon Indicator: How To Use It For Cryptocurrency Trading ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/aroon-indicator-how-to-use-it-for-cryptocurrency-trading-ievjzpn7e3c )
This article helps to understand the Aroon Indicator, also known as Aroon Oscillator. In this blog, you will learn about how to use it in cryptocurrency trading.
Recommended IDE for Data Scientists and Machine Learning Engineers ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/recommended-ide-for-data-scientists-and-machine-learning-engineers-c07vd112nsw )
An overview of the development environments for data scientists and machine learning engineers programming in R, Python, Scala, and Julia.
That's all for now. Have a great week!

16635003a8a46233,Gabriel from DataCamp ,What is Data Engineering?,2018-10-02,Demystifying Crucial Statistics in Python. For Loops in R. Customer Segmentation in Python. Writing R code the right way. Convolutional Neural Networks. Feature Selection in Python. And more! DataCamp,"[

Demystifying Crucial Statistics in Python. For Loops in R. Customer Segmentation in Python. Writing R code the right way. Convolutional Neural Networks. Feature Selection in Python. And more!

Hello - this week's featured top posts explore what data engineering is, convolutional neural networks, writing R code the right way, For Loops in R, introducing customer segmentation in Python and much more!

In this week's DataFramed episode, Hugo Bowne-Anderson speaks with Vicki Boykis about what full-stack end-to-end data science actually is and how it works in a consulting setting across various industries. Check it out!
In this blog, you will learn what data engineering entails along with learning about our future data engineering course offerings.
Learn about the basic statistics required for Data Science and Machine Learning in Python.
Introduction to Customer Segmentation in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/introduction-customer-segmentation-python )
In this tutorial, you're going to learn how to implement customer segmentation using RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) analysis from scratch in Python.
Beginner's Guide to Feature Selection in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/feature-selection-python )
Learn about the basics of feature selection and how to implement and investigate various feature selection techniques in Python.
In A Nutshell: Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/convolutional-neural-network-cnn-in-a-nutshell-1tjyeh8p43h )
In this article, you will learn about the convolution operation, padding, pooling, convolutional layers and CNN architecture with graphical illustrations.
R Best Practices: R you writing the R way! ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/r-best-practices-r-you-writing-the-r-way-ng442twxpe )
This post covers some of the R programming best practices that can be implemented by programmers to improve code readability, consistency, and repeatability.

Unlike binary classification (0 or 1), we need multiple probabilities at the output layer of the neural network. This article explains the softmax activation function which is mostly used for classification problems for multiple probabilities.
This tutorial takes course material from DataCamp's Intermediate R for Finance course and allows you to practice For Loops.
Architecture Explained of R Package for IB IBrokers ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/architecture-explained-of-r-package-for-ib-ibrokers-36yomxrtrt7 )
This article gives a detailed overview of the architecture of the IBrokers package which is the R implementation of Interactive Brokers API.

Issue #63. Comparing Keras and TensorFlow. 7 resume tips for early analytics careers. Tensors with PyTorch. Understanding boxplots and much more!

column1: We're excited to share our Community content this week! Starting with a comparison of Keras and TensorFlow for deep neural networks, followed by 7 resume tips for early analytics careers, tensors with PyTorch, understanding boxplots and much more!

As usual, we also have a brand new podcast episode this week! What are the paths to becoming a data scientist, common data scientist profiles, and how to figure out which ones may be a fit for you? Find out in episode 40 of DataFramed, where Hugo Bowne-Anderson speaks with Renée Teate from HelioCampus!
Is Keras more efficient than TensorFlow on Deep Neural Networks? ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-keras-is-more-efficient-than-tensorflow-on-deep-neural-networks-tasgm2z29ln )

In the previous module, we implemented a neural network application on E-commerce data set. Now, we will build the same application using Keras. In this module, we will learn that building a neural network application using Keras is much simpler compared to TensorFlow.
Deep Learning: Artificial Neural Network Using TensorFlow In Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/deep-learning-artificial-neural-network-using-tensorflow-in-python-hb0c6jgbkpt )
In this article, we develop a Machine Learning technique called Deep Learning (Artificial Neural Network) by using Tensorflow and predicting stock price in Python.
Deduce the Number of Layers and Neurons for ANN ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/layers-neurons-artificial-neural-networks )

There is an optimal number of hidden layers and neurons for an artificial neural network (ANN). This tutorial discusses a simple approach for determining the optimal numbers of layers and neurons for ANN's.
How to predict output with only examples without any ML model? ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-predict-the-output-with-only-examples-without-any-ml-model-n2j3tl8489e )

K Nearest Neighbor is the simplest supervised machine learning algorithm. KNN is not explicitly learning a model and predicting the output by looking all the exampled together. It makes the algorithm simple with minimal training phase.
7 More Resume Tips for Early Career Analytics Professionals ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/7-more-resume-tips-for-early-career-analytics-professionals-2a60npc62r9 )

Our experts tackle common resume questions from analytics professionals including how to communicate your analytics experience effectively, how to write resume bullets, and what to include (or not include) when it comes to hobbies and side data projects.
In this tutorial, you'll learn about Tensors, PyTorch, and how to create a simple neural network with PyTorch.

A boxplot is a standardized way of displaying the distribution of data based on a five number summary (minimum, first quartile (Q1), median, third quartile (Q3), and maximum). It can tell you about your outliers and what their values are. It can also tell you if your data is symmetrical and more.
Data Science at Stitch Fix (with Eric Colson) ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/podcast/data-science-stitch-fix )
Hugo speaks with Eric Colson, Chief Algorithms Officer at Stitch Fix.
Machine Learning eCommerce: How It Is Redefining Retail And Sales ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/machine-learning-ecommerce-how-it-is-redefining-retail-and-sales-w0cugbjlezb )
The eCommerce industry is growing across the world. From what started as a few stores that enabled online shopping
column2: today, the smallest of brands are able to take their products online and market them to a large consumer base.

column1: Credit Card Fraud Detection Using Machine Learning ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/credit-card-fraud-detection-using-machine-learning-algorithm-8dyh3fefvrb )

Credit card companies are able to recognize fraudulent credit card transactions so that customers are not charged for items that they did not purchase. This article covers how to implement machine learning based credit card fraud detection.
Popular Python Trading Platforms For Algorithmic Trading ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/popular-python-trading-platforms-for-algorithmic-trading-d8yxnm2m5n5 )
Learn about the most popular python trading platforms and the most widely used python-based libraries for quantitative trading.
How to Implement Neural Network Model Using TensorFlow? ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-implement-neural-network-model-using-tensorflow-opq8lyvcska )

TensorFlow makes it simple to implement a neural network model. Here, you will implement a neural network application using TensorFlow on an E-commerce dataset. You will learn how to predict the yearly amount spent by each customer based on their browsing behavior.
Time Series Analysis: Working With datetime Data In Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/time-series-analysis-working-with-date-time-data-in-python-2m61bl63fbm )

This article discusses some important tools that are really helpful for traders to analyse time series data as well as design and backtest trading strategies. This blog focuses on how to deal with dates, frequency of the time series and more!
Option Chain Extraction For NSE Stocks Using Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/option-chain-extraction-for-nse-stocks-using-python-do1gufqz1ru )
This article explains how to scrape web data using Python and how to extract Option chain data for the stocks listed on the National Stock Exchange of India.

Pros and cons of the top 11 algorithms every machine learning engineer should know.

We also have a new DataFramed episode where Hugo speaks with Tanya Cashorali about data science consulting in health &amp

column1: How to Implement Machine Learning Based Recommendation Systems ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-implement-machine-learning-based-recommendation-systems-xxdksc695i )
This module covers how to implement machine learning based recommendation systems.
How to Utilize K Means Clustering Model for Unsupervised ML Problems ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-utilize-k-means-clustering-model-for-unsupervised-ml-problems-5xlxzlv1nwv )
This article covers K Means Clustering which is an unsupervised machine learning algorithm. It is very efficient and mostly used for content based recommendation systems.
Kalman Filter Techniques And Statistical Arbitrage In China's Futures ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/kalman-filter-techniques-and-statistical-arbitrage-in-chinas-futures-3y91y7eyz4l )

The project focuses on China's futures market using Statistical Arbitrage and Pair trading techniques. You will run an Augmented Dickey-Fuller test on the spread to confirm statistically whether the series is mean reverting or not, and will calculate Kalman Filter regression on the spread series.
Getting Started With Python For Trading ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/getting-started-with-python-for-trading-qya94up6a0c )

Python is widely used in the field of machine learning and now trading. This article covers all that is required to get started with Python. It can be used to code your own trading strategies and test them.
Predicting Popularity of The New York Times Comments (Part 1) ( https://datacritics.com/2018/08/25/predicting-popularity-of-new-york-times-comments-part-1/ )
DataCamp user sakshigupta88's 2018 summer capstone project!
Using Quadratic Discriminant Analysis To Optimize An Intraday Momentum ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/using-quadratic-discriminant-analysis-to-optimize-an-intraday-momentum-3376re95h7k )

This article explains how to create an intraday momentum strategy and to use QDA as a means of optimizing our strategy. Beginning by reviewing Linear Discriminant Analysis or LDA and how it is associated with QDA, gaining an understanding of QDA and when we might implement this technique instead.
Calculating Value At Risk In Excel &amp

This post will take you through the step-by-step process to understand and compute VaR in Excel and Python using Historical Method and Variance-Covariance approach. You can also download the excel and Python codes to calculate the VaR for yourself.
How I got in the top 1% on Kaggle ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-i-got-in-the-top-1-on-kaggle-data-science-tutorials-qql86282mnb )
This author participated in Santander Customer Satisfaction challenge, ran on Kaggle for 2 months and got into the top 1%. Here, he discusses his approach to this problem.
Beyond the Unicorn: 4 Developing Data Scientist Career Paths ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/beyond-the-unicorn-4-developing-data-scientist-career-paths-54sppq3cfj3 )
As the data science market continues to evolve, we examine four growing specialty areas within data science that are in increasingly high demand.

Hi there,

column1: We’ve been busy here at DataCamp. We’ve recently launched 3 new Courses and 1 new Project for you to expand your data science skills. Check them out below!
Preprocessing for Machine Learning in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/preprocessing-for-machine-learning-in-python?utm_source=customerio&amp

This Python course covers the basics of how and when to perform data preprocessing. You'll learn how to standardize your data so that it's in the right form for your model, create new features, and select the best features to improve your model fit. Finally, you'll have some practice preprocessing by getting a dataset on UFO sightings (yes, you read that correctly) ready for
Convolutional Neural Networks for Image Processing ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/convolutional-neural-networks-for-image-processing?utm_source=customerio&amp

Convolutional neural networks are deep learning algorithms that are particularly powerful for analysis of images. This Python course will teach you how to construct, train and evaluate convolutional neural networks. You will also learn how to improve their ability to learn from data, and how to interpret the results of the training.

Automatically generate keywords for a search engine marketing campaign using Python. In this Project, you will pretend to work for a digital marketing agency. You are approached by a massive online retailer of furniture and are tasked with creating a prototype set of keywords for search campaigns for their sofas section.
Have you ever wondered what goes into designing a survey and how survey responses are turned into actionable

insights? In this course, you will model survey data from the National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey using R's survey and tidyverse packages. Following the course, you will be able to successfully interpret survey results and finally find the answers to life's burning questions!

1655caa6351608fe,Gabriel from DataCamp ,The Fall of The Simpsons,2018-08-21,"Build a ggplot. Logistic Regression. What is AI? Predicting Employee Churn. Data Science in Finance. Career move to Big Data. SAS, R or Python? DataCamp ISSUE #60 — AUGUST 21, 2018 Hi there - this","[

Build a ggplot. Logistic Regression. What is AI? Predicting Employee Churn. Data Science in Finance. Career move to Big Data. SAS, R or Python?
Hi there - this week's top Community posts include a rating analysis of The Simpsons, logistic regression, AI basics, career advice and more! We hope you enjoy this one.

We also have a new DataFramed episode! Hugo Bowne-Anderson speaks with Christie Bahlai, Assistant Professor at Kent State University, about data science, ecology, and the adoption of techniques such as machine learning in academic research. What is happening in scientific research at the interface between data science &amp
column2: machine learning methods? Is there a paradigm shift occurring here? Listen to find out!

column1: Build-a-ggplot: The Fall of The Simpsons ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/build-a-ggplot-the-fall-of-the-simpsons-5p2oaf8r62w )
Scrape episode ratings of The Simpsons and learn to customize a ggplot with annotations, highlights, and theme modifications!
Extracting Insights from Data Using Logistic Regression ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/how-to-play-with-data-using-logistic-regression-model-ju0zjszaxx )
Learn how to create machine learning models for classification or logistic regression problems. Practice with two different datasets and learn the basic techniques for creating models.
Deep Dive Into The Basics of Artificial Neural Network ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/dive-deep-in-to-the-basics-of-artificial-neural-network-6uac88q224f )

Learn how to create machine learning models for artificial neural networks. Practice with the MNIST dataset and learn the technique for creating a simple model. You will use Tensorflow, a software framework for building and deploying machine learning models.
What is AI? Training vs Inference AI? ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/what-is-ai-training-vs-inference-ai-bks7v3j80qc )

Although there is often lots of hype surrounding Artificial Intelligence (AI), once we strip away the marketing fluff, what is revealed is a rapidly developing technology that is already changing our lives. But to fully appreciate its potential, we need to understand what it is and what it is not!
Analyze employee churn. Find out why employees are leaving the company, and learn to predict who will leave the company.
An intriguing dive into the world of dimensionality reduction.
Hyperparameter Optimization in Machine Learning Models ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/parameter-optimization-machine-learning-models )
This tutorial covers what a parameter and a hyperparameter are in a machine learning model along with why it is vital in order to enhance your model's performance.
Why Big Data Is the Best Career Move in 2018 ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/huge-job-options-are-the-reason-why-big-data-is-the-best-career-move-i-zpemahi3cv )
Huge job options are the reason why big data is the best career move in 2018 across different industry verticals.
2018 SAS, R, or Python Extended Analysis ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/news/2018-sas-r-or-python-extended-analysis-u9it0ll8bn )
This video takes a closer look at the developing 3-year trends from a SAS, R, or Python flash survey, and gives advice about which tool you should learn.
Data Science in Finance (with Yves Hilpisch) ( https://www.datacamp.com/community/podcast/data-science-finance )
The financial world has been irrecoverably changed by the advent of data science. Find out how.
That's all for now. Have a great week!

Hi there,

column1: We have launched three new courses in the past two weeks! Two in Python and one in R. Check them out below if youâ€™re interested in learning about Bayesian data analysis, police activity, and portfolio management!
Intro to Portfolio Risk Management in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/intro-to-portfolio-risk-management-in-python?utm_source=customerio&amp

This course will teach you how to evaluate basic portfolio risk and returns like a quantitative analyst on Wall Street. This is the most critical step towards being able to fully automate your portfolio construction and management processes. Discover what factors are driving your portfolio returns, construct market-cap
weighted equity portfolios, and learn how to forecast and hedge market risk via scenario generation.
Fundamentals of Bayesian Data Analysis in R ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/fundamentals-of-bayesian-data-analysis-in-r?utm_source=customerio&amp

Bayesian data analysis is an approach to statistical modeling and machine learning that is becoming more and more popular. It provides a uniform framework to build problem-specific models that can be used for both statistical inference and for prediction. This course will introduce you to Bayesian data analysis: what it is, how it works, and why it is a useful tool to have in your data science toolbox.

This course will give you the chance to apply your Python and pandas knowledge by answering interesting questions about a real dataset! You will explore the Stanford Open Policing Project dataset and analyze the impact of gender on police behavior. During the course, you will gain more practice cleaning messy data, creating visualizations, combining and reshaping datasets, and manipulating time series data. Analyzing Police Activity with pandas will give you valuable experience analyzing a dataset from start to finish, preparing you for your data science career.

164d19706a1731ae,Martijn from DataCamp <team@datacamp.com>,New Courses & Project!,2018-07-25,"Hi there, We have a lot of new content this week: two new R Courses and one new R Project. By taking these, you&#39
column2:
ll get more familiar with data cleaning and visualization, statistics, experimental","[

Hi there,

column1: We have a lot of new content this week: two new R Courses and one new R Project. By taking these, you’ll get more familiar with data cleaning and visualization, statistics, experimental design, and structural equation modeling amongst other things.

If someone is asking a question then collecting data to try and answer it, they're doing an experiment! In this course, you'll learn about basic experimental design, including block and factorial designs. Throughout the course, you'll work with open data from a loan company to design both single and multiple factor experiments plus an A/B test.
Additionally, you’ll work with an open health dataset to learn how to utilize blocking in experiments to make experimental groups more similar.

Do women live longer than men? Is life expectancy increasing? In this Project, you will answer these questions and much more by manipulating and visualizing United Nations life expectancy data using the R package ggplot2. Since this dataset contains historical information, you will also be able to visualize how life expectancy evolved in recent years.
Structural Equation Modeling with lavaan in R ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/structural-equation-modeling-with-lavaan-in-r?utm_source=customerio&amp

When working with data, we often want a deep understanding of how our data is connected or structured. In this course, you will learn how to create measurement models of your data, which are often used to confirm the structure of a scale or questionnaire. Following this course, you will be able to dive into your data and gain a much deeper understanding of how it all fits together.

""Data science"" can be hard to define, and the definition is constantly evolving. We thought it would be helfpul to share a working definition since you're just getting started with us.

column1: Learn the entire data science workflow ( https://www.datacamp.com )
Data Science is the interdisciplinary process of importing, cleaning, manipulating, modeling, and visualizing data.

At DataCamp, you will use Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:python ), R ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:r ), and SQL ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:sql ) to explore all aspects of data science, using techniques from computer science, mathematics, statistics, and more.
Data science is used in nearly every discipline, including business, healthcare, law, engineering, and more.
There is currently a huge demand for qualified data scientists.
Data Scientist"" was ranked the best job in America in 2016.
